# Hire + onboard a new product-team dev in 2 weeks

## Context

From signed offer to first merged PR + first on-call shadow. New hire understands repo layout, runs the dev loop locally, has ship-ready CLAUDE.md/AGENTS.md context, knows incident protocol, and has a named buddy. Output: 30/60/90-day plan filed, first PR merged, retro by day 14.

## Outcome

By the end of this playbook, the operator has run the 5 stages below and produced the written decision artefact in the final stage.

Success criteria:

- All 5 stages have written outputs in the project record
- Each stage's decision gate was answered before advancing (yes / no in writing)
- Final stage produced the required written decision artifact
- Every methodology reference loaded cleanly via `faion get-content`

## Steps

### 1. Role Spec

Write the role and bar before the first interview.

Tasks:
- Write the 1-page JD: outputs, stack, seniority, comp band
- Define interview rubric and bar with hiring panel
- Pre-script the take-home + system-design prompts

Outputs:
- JD
- rubric + bar
- interview prompts

Decision gate: Advance only when panel signs off on rubric and bar.

### 2. Source

Get to 6-8 qualified candidates fast.

Tasks:
- Post in 2 channels + ask team for referrals
- Screen for stack, seniority, and timezone fit
- Schedule loop with 6-8 qualified candidates

Outputs:
- sourcing log
- screening notes
- scheduled loops

Decision gate: Advance when at least 6 qualified candidates are in the loop.

### 3. Interview Loop

Same loop for every candidate, scored independently.

Tasks:
- Run the loop: take-home, system design, behavioral, peer
- Scorecard within 24h per interviewer, no group debate first
- Hold the calibration meeting after all scorecards in

Outputs:
- scorecards
- calibration notes
- hire/no-hire decisions

Decision gate: Advance only when at least 1 hire-bar candidate has cleared calibration.

### 4. Offer & Sign

Move fast once the bar is cleared.

Tasks:
- Send offer same-week as calibration
- Negotiate within the band only
- Sign and set the start date

Outputs:
- offer doc
- signed contract
- start date on calendar

Decision gate: Advance when contract is countersigned.

### 5. Onboard in 2 Weeks

Productive on day 14.

Tasks:
- Day 1-3: access, docs, intros, dev env
- Week 1: first PR shipped (small but real)
- Week 2: first end-to-end ticket shipped to prod

Outputs:
- onboarding checklist
- first PR merged
- first prod ticket shipped

Decision gate: Required output: a prod ticket shipped by end of week 2.

## Decision points

- Stage 1 (Role Spec): Advance only when panel signs off on rubric and bar.
- Stage 2 (Source): Advance when at least 6 qualified candidates are in the loop.
- Stage 3 (Interview Loop): Advance only when at least 1 hire-bar candidate has cleared calibration.
- Stage 4 (Offer & Sign): Advance when contract is countersigned.
- Stage 5 (Onboard in 2 Weeks): Required output: a prod ticket shipped by end of week 2.

